Southern Youth Peace Initiative, (SYPI), has called on the business magnate, Chief Evarestus Nnaji to contest the forthcoming 2023 Enugu State governorship election in Enugu state. The group assured to give Nnaji 100 percent of their support should he agree to contest. Southern Youth Peace Initiative, SYPI, is a conglomerate of all the youths across the Southern region of Nigeria with a headquarters in Enugu. Gov Emmanuel Wants Former Aspirants To Support Ekiti PDP… 2023: Fayemi’s Wife Denies Senatorial Ambition The group led by the President, Ikejiofor Onochie, and the Secretary, Ikechukwu Oraka, in a statement on Friday said they have looked into Nnaji’s track records and found him worthy to succeed Gov. Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi, come 2023 and consolidate on his good works. “As the forthcoming election is fast approaching, we consider Enugu State our priority as the heartbeat of Eastern Nigeria. “We painstakingly researched on the family background, political foundation, indelible impacts, cognate experiences and passion for the service to humanity, and our regional association found you worthy as youth-friendly as well a candidate who can contest, win and continue with the development agenda of His Excellency Rt. Hon Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi led administration. “We therefore kindly request without any fear of any contradiction, an iota of any doubt, and with absolute conviction of your victory to contest the gubernatorial election of Enugu State come 2023. “The Southern Youth Peace Initiative has resolved to give you our 100% support as we have done to many past and serving governors of Nigeria. Accept the assurances of our greatest regards,” the group assures.